text.tspan: Share of students achieving minimum learning outcomes, 1975 to 2015
Proportion of students achieving a minimum proficiency benchmark. Achievement outcomes come from
standardized, psychometrically-robust international and regional tests. In order to maximize coverage by country,
tests have been harmonized and pooled across subjects (math, reading, science) and levels (primary and secondary
education). See source for details on proficiency benchmarks.
